<collectingCountry box="[359,479,1524,1548]" name="Cameroon" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="224" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,618,1620]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1559,1584]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[856,949,1559,1584]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">cucullus</emphasis>
(= cap, hood), referring to the hood-shaped signum in the female genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
